                            <comment id="17273265" author="reta" created="Thu, 28 Jan 2021 02:37:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ffang&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ffang&quot;&gt;ffang&lt;/a&gt; do you recall this change? I am wondering if throwing an exception is the way to go (since `verify` never returns `false` in fact), thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17273764" author="ffang" created="Thu, 28 Jan 2021 14:30:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=reta&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;reta&quot;&gt;reta&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

